column5: Any one seeing any action yet??  I spotted a Chironomidae midge yesterday, and a winter stone fly a few weeks back.  Anyone seeing any blue-winged olives??  -R-
I've not been close enough to any stream or river to dip my net... But I got that itch fer sure, and this time its not one that requires a cream!  Soon...oh yes....soon!

Ohh dang, i have procrastinated my tying for way too damn long now... BWO tying time  dont want to have to run out on the water... I will be looking next time I am on the river, which hopefully is tomorrow

Stone fly hatch was very late here this year, I only began to see numbers of them this week, last week fish were sipping something off the surface in good number, I assume it was stone flys, from my fishing log everything seems a bit later this year.
Saw my first 'skeeter of 2008 yesterday on the window pane beside my recliner... quickly squashed it to smithereens...
Fighting the war we will never win.  Carry on good soilder
seen a few stone flys myself and i imagine what was a midge not sure though

Saw a few more insects buzzing around my balcony today. With this nice warm weather they all should start moving around a little more. If i wasn't so busy with end of term work i'd be down at the river.
I have been watching alot lately  2 of my buddies wifes are due any day to hatch!!!   and man those will be some big insects that will come out!!! LOL!!!!
